text: Marie Josephine Hull (née Sherwood; January 3, 1877 – March 12, 1957) was an American actress. She won an Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress for the movie Harvey (1950). Hull died on March 12, 1957, aged 80, from a cerebral hemorrhage in The Bronx.Stage star Josephine Hull dies, news.google.com; accessed January 16, 2016. ==References== Category:1877 births Category:1957 deaths Category:American movie actors Category:American television actors Category:American stage actors Category:American radio actors Category:Actors from Massachusetts Category:Deaths from cerebral hemorrhage Category:People from Newton, Massachusetts Category:American Academy Award winning actors Category:Golden Globe Award winning actors
